                <div class="comment_desc mt-3 md:ml-0 -ml-16">
                    The Digital Millennium Copyright Act, or DMCA, is a 1998 law passed in the US and is among the worldâ€™s first laws recognising intellectual property on the internet. Signed into law by the then US President Bill Clinton, the law oversees the implementation of the two treaties signed and agreed upon by member nations of the World Intellectual Property Organisation (WIPO) in 1996.
                </div>

